   "text": "Write a program that takes a list of numbers and calculates the sum and average of those numbers. The program should be able to handle any number of inputs and should output both the sum and the average. The inputs will be provided as a list, and you must ensure to handle cases where the list is empty."
  }
 ],
 "skeleton_code": "program SumAndAverage\n\n    dictionary\n        numbers: list of integer\n        sum: integer\n        average: real\n        count: integer\n    enddictionary\n\n    procedure calculateSumAndAverage(numbers: list of integer) \n        sum <- 0\n        count <- length of numbers\n        for each number in numbers do\n            sum <- sum + number\n        endfor\n        if count > 0 then\n            average <- sum / count\n        else\n            average <- 0\n        endif\n    endprocedure\n\n    algorithm\n        input numbers\n        call calculateSumAndAverage(numbers)\n        output sum, average\n    endalgorithm\n\nendprogram",
